Breizh Software Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is used when you use TimeMonitor.

PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT

We don't collect any of your information.

PERSONNAL INFORMATION ACCESSED BY TIMEMONITOR

In order to work, TimeMonitor doesn't need personnal information

HOW DO WE USE YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION?

TimeMonitor doesn't use any personnal information

SHARING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION

We won't share your information because we don't collect them.

YOUR RIGHTS
If you are a European resident, you have the right to access personal information we hold about you and to ask that your personal information be corrected, updated, or deleted. If you would like to exercise this right, please contact us through the contact information below.

Additionally, if you are a European resident we note that we are processing your information in order to fulfill contracts we might have with you (for example if you make an order through the Site), or otherwise to pursue our legitimate business interests listed above.  Additionally, please note that your information will not be transferred outside of Europe.

DATA RETENTION
You data will never be stored.

CHANGES
We may update this privacy policy from time to time in order to reflect, for example, changes to our practices or for other operational, legal or regulatory reasons.

CONTACT US
For more information about our privacy practices, if you have questions, or if you would like to make a complaint, please contact us by e-mail at guillaume.brouillon@outlook.fr.
